{"sectionId":684,"sectionIdLiteral":"684","humanId":"lesson-268","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Let all things be exactly as they are.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 268"},"annotation":"W-268","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-268\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"684#1\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Let me not be Your critic, Lord, today, and judge against You.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Let me not attempt to interfere with Your creation, and distort it into sickly forms.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Let me be willing to withdraw my wishes from its unity, and thus to let it be as You created it.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>For thus will I be able, too, to recognize my Self as You created me.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>In love was I created, and in love will I remain forever.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>What can frighten me, when I let all things be exactly as they are?</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"684#2\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Let not our sight be blasphemous today, nor let our ears attend to lying tongues.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Only reality is free of pain.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Only reality is free of loss.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#2:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Only reality is wholly safe.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"684#2:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>And it is only this we seek today.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Let me not be Your critic, Lord, today, and judge against You. Let me not attempt to interf